{
  "id": "019d286c-c8e3-7462-a4e5-9bd4f0aa3db1",
  "content": "r>\n    Give AI the right tools to close the feedback loop,<br>\n    and it goes from frustrating to genuinely useful.</p>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"flex-grow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">07 / 08</div>\n</div>\n<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n<!-- SLIDE 8: TAKEAWAYS                              -->\n<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n<div class=\"slide\" style=\"background: linear-gradient(160deg, #0f172a 0%, #1a2332 50%, #0f172a 100%);\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\">Key Takeaways</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\">\n    What I Learned<br>\n    <span class=\"highlight-green\">Building UI with AI</span>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"takeaway-list\">\n    <div class=\"takeaway-item\">\n      <div class=\"takeaway-icon\">&#128065;</div>\n      <div class=\"takeaway-text\">\n        <strong>AI can code UI. It can't see UI.</strong><br>\n        <span style=\"color: var(--text-secondary);\">Valid CSS doesn't mean correct layout.<br>The rendering gap is real.</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"takeaway-item\">\n      <div class=\"takeaway-icon\">&#128196;</div>\n      <div class=\"takeaway-text\">\n        <strong>Alignment is the failure mode.</strong><br>\n        <span style=\"color: var(--text-secondary);\">Text overflow, element overlap, misalignment<br>&mdash; the same issues every time.</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"takeaway-item\">\n      <div class=\"takeaway-icon\">&#128295;</div>\n      <div class=\"takeaway-text\">\n        <strong>Tools beat prompts.</strong><br>\n        <span style=\"color: var(--text-secondary);\">No amount of \"be careful with alignment\"<br>in a prompt fixes this. A screenshot helps.</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"takeaway-item\">\n      <div class=\"takeaway-icon\">&#128161;</div>\n      <div class=\"takeaway-text\">\n        <strong>Context engineering &gt; prompt engineering.</strong><br>\n        <span style=\"color: var(--text-secondary);\">Don't ask AI to be better. Give it the right<br>tools to close the loop.</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>",
